# 詞: 銀包  

1. 我今日落街前先檢查一下銀包有冇帶錢同咭。 (I checked my wallet before going out today to see if I had money and cards.)  
2. 佢嘅銀包係真皮嘅，摸起來好有質感。 (His wallet is made of genuine leather, feels high quality.)  
3. 如果你遺失銀包，請盡快報警同聯絡銀行凍結咭。 (If you lose your wallet, please report to the police and contact the bank to block the cards ASAP.)  
4. 我同朋友去日本旅行，帶多個銀包裝不同貨幣，方便換匯。 (I and my friend went to Japan, brought multiple wallets holding different currencies for easy exchange.)  
5. 今次促銷期間，銀包減價百分之三十，真係好平。 (During this promotion, wallets are 30% off, really cheap.)  
6. 佢哋小朋友學會自己整理銀包，教導佢哋負責任。 (The kids learned to organize their own wallets, teaching them responsibility.)  
7. 我發現銀包內有張舊咭，已經過期啦，要換新嘅。 (I found an expired card in my wallet, need to replace it.)  
8. 雨天行街時，我會用防水套裝住銀包，防止濕水。 (On rainy days, I put my wallet in a waterproof cover to keep it dry.)  
9. 佢每日早晨先檢查銀包有冇身份證，再出門上班。 (He checks his wallet for his ID every morning before heading to work.)  
10. 我送女朋友一個刻有她名字嘅銀包作為生日禮物，她好開心。 (I gave my girlfriend a wallet engraved with her name as a birthday gift; she was very happy.) [end of text]


